byline.contributor: Jaime Yaya Barry reported from Banjul, and Dionne Searcey from Dakar, Senegal.
byline.original: By JAIME YAYA BARRY and DIONNE SEARCEY

lead_paragraph: The president, Adama Barrow, had fled to neighboring Senegal more than a week earlier after Yahya Jammeh, his defeated predecessor, refused to cede power.
